[src:shadow-dom/api-shadowroot] In the `updateStyle()` function itself, we get a reference to the shadow DOM using `Element.shadowRoot`.
[src:shadow-dom/attachshadow] The **`attachShadow()`** method of the `Element` interface attaches a shadow DOM tree to the specified element and returns a reference to its `ShadowRoot`.
[src:shadow-dom/attachshadow] A string specifying the *encapsulation mode* for the shadow DOM tree.
[src:shadow-dom/attachshadow] Elements inside the shadow root are accessible from JavaScript via the element's `shadowRoot` property.
[src:shadow-dom/attachshadow] Elements inside the shadow root cannot be accessed from JavaScript via the `shadowRoot` property, which is set to `null`.
[src:shadow-dom/attachshadow] A boolean that specifies whether the shadow root is clonable: when set to `true`, the shadow host cloned with `Node.cloneNode()` or `Document.importNode()` will include shadow root in the copy.
[src:shadow-dom/attachshadow] A `CustomElementRegistry` that will be used as the scoped custom element registry of the attached shadow root.
[src:shadow-dom/attachshadow] If `null` or `undefined`, the shadow root will use the global registry referenced by `Window.customElements`.
[src:shadow-dom/attachshadow] A boolean that, when set to `true`, specifies behavior that mitigates custom element issues around focusability.
[src:shadow-dom/attachshadow] When a non-focusable part of the shadow DOM is clicked, the first focusable part is given focus, and the shadow host is given any available `:focus` styling.
[src:shadow-dom/attachshadow] A string value that indicates the effective target of any element reference made against the shadow host from outside the host element.
[src:shadow-dom/attachshadow] A boolean that, when set to `true`, indicates that the shadow root is serializable.
[src:shadow-dom/attachshadow] If set, the shadow root may be serialized by calling the `Element.getHTML()` or `ShadowRoot.getHTML()` methods with the `options.serializableShadowRoots` parameter set `true`.
[src:shadow-dom/attachshadow] A string specifying the *slot assignment mode* for the shadow DOM tree.
[src:shadow-dom/attachshadow] Elements are automatically assigned to `<slot>` elements within this shadow root.
[src:shadow-dom/attachshadow] Any top-level children of the host with a `slot` attribute which matches the `name` attribute of a `<slot>` within this shadow root will be assigned to that slot.
[src:shadow-dom/attachshadow] Any top-level children of the host with no `slot` attribute will be assigned to the first `<slot>` with no `name` attribute (the "default slot"), if one is present.
[src:shadow-dom/attachshadow] Elements are manually assigned to particular slot elements using `HTMLSlotElement.assign()`.
[src:shadow-dom/attachshadow] The **`Element.attachShadow()`** method attaches a shadow DOM tree to the specified element and returns a reference to its `ShadowRoot`.
[src:shadow-dom/attachshadow] This is the programmatic mechanism to create a `ShadowRoot`, which is the root node of a Shadow DOM attached to a host element (it is also possible to create a `ShadowRoot` declaratively using the `shadowrootmode` attribute of the `<template>` element).
[src:shadow-dom/attachshadow] It is used for creating custom elements.
[src:shadow-dom/attachshadow] Note that you can't attach a shadow root to every type of element.
[src:shadow-dom/attachshadow] There are some that can't have a shadow DOM for security reasons (for example `<a>`).
[src:shadow-dom/attachshadow] The method may be called on an element that already has a declarative shadow root, provided the specified mode `mode` matches the existing mode.
[src:shadow-dom/attachshadow] In this case the `ShadowRoot` that was already present will be cleared and returned.
[src:shadow-dom/attachshadow] This allows for cases where, for example, server-side rendering has already declaratively created a shadow root, and then client-side code attempts to attach the root again.
[src:shadow-dom/attachshadow] Otherwise calling `attachShadow()` on an element that already has a shadow root will throw an exception.
[src:shadow-dom/attachshadow] A shadow root can be attached with an encapsulation mode, which is specified as either `open` or `closed`.
[src:shadow-dom/attachshadow] If the `{mode: "open"}` argument is passed, the host element's `shadowRoot` property can subsequently be used to get the attached shadow root.
[src:shadow-dom/attachshadow] If `{mode: "closed"}` is passed then the Element's `shadowRoot` property is set to `null`.
[src:shadow-dom/attachshadow] Note that JavaScript can still access a closed shadow root by storing the value returned by the function.
